<h2>
	<table width=100%>
		<tr>
			<td align="left"><a name="general" style="font-style: normal">General</a></td>
			<td align="right"><a class="internal" href="#" style="font-size: 12px">Back to top</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
</h2>
	<p>Some species of the <i>Saccharomycetes</i> clade translate the Leucine codon CUG as Serine. This webserver is designed to detect if your species uses yeast alternative codon usage or not. Therefore, you need to upload genome data. In this data, motor proteins are predicted and aligned with reference data from <a class = "external" href="http://www.cymobase.org/cymobase" target = "_blank">CymoBase</a>. The aligned predicted CUG positions are basis for the codon usage prediction.</p>


<h2>
	<table width=100%>
		<tr>
			<td align="left"><a name="entering" style="font-style: normal">Entering the query data</a></td>
			<td align="right"><a class="internal" href="#" style="font-size: 12px">Back to top</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
</h2>
	<p>Use the file upload button to upload your query data. Query data may be complete genome files as well as EST data. Query data must be in fasta format. Please note that the file upload is restricted to 15MB file size. To upload larger files, please contact us.</p>

<h2>
	<table width=100%>
		<tr>
			<td align="left"><a name="settings" style="font-style: normal">Setting Bagheera's gene prediction options</a></td>
